snippet.title: Cannes Film Festival: Amber Heard leads departures at Nice airport
snippet.description: They've been displaying their glamorous sense of style at a number of the star-studded French Riviera events so far.Yet unfortunately it was time to say goodbye to the Cannes Film Festival as Amber Heard led the departures at Nice airport, France, on Sunday.The American actress, 32, joined models Irina Shayk and Jasmine Tookes as they left the French city after a fun-filled few days.Amber cut a stylish figure for the airport visit as she showed off her slender frame in a pair of skinny jeans and a white t-shirt.She teamed the ensemble with an oversized grey blazer for an elegant finish to her look.Trying to keep a low profile, a make-up free Amber added an oversized black hat, heels and handbag as she made her way across the terminals.The Rum Diary actress appeared rushed off her feet as she frantically ran through the airport and ducked under barriers.Yet she still had time to sign some autographs for her loyal fans who flocked to her in the busy building.The model, 32, opted for comfortable footwear as she added a pair of box-fresh white, grey and pink trainers.Irina, who has a one-year-old daughter with Bradley Cooper, tried to keep a low profile as she added a pair of oversized black sunglasses.Adding a glamorous twist to her ensemble, she added a black leather handbag and pendant necklace to her look.Irina styled her brunette locks into a low ponytail as she made her way through the airport and added a slick of make-up.Victoria's Secret Angel, Jasmine, also cut a casual figure to depart the Cannes Film Festival on Sunday.The 27-year-old looked pretty in pink as she showed off her model physique in a pair of grey tracksuit bottoms and a pink jumper.Jasmine looked radiant as she went make-up free and styled her brunette locks into a high bun, which showed off her enviable cheekbones.The model wheeled a Louis Vuitton carry-on case as well as a black duffel bag on her shoulder, she completed her look with silver earrings and black slide on sandals.Jasmine appeared in good spirits as she smiled and beamed at photographers, no doubt after a few fun-filled days in Cannes.Also leaving the French city was talented actor and filmmaker, Spike Lee, 61.Spike cut a very trendy and casual look in a navy blue New York Yankees tracksuit, with a patchwork denim jacket over the top.The producer opted for red accessories as he added red and white Nike trainers, a red backpack and red headphones.He also wore a long gold chain with a pendant on it, clear glasses and a black baseball cap.Spike also joined Czech model, Eva Herzigová, 45, as she arrived at the Nice airport.The make-up free actress kept a very low profile as she wore wide-leg black trousers with a white shirt and a dark cape over the top.Eva styled her blonde locks into a pulled back hairdo, as she added oversized dark sunglasses.This year's Cannes Film Festival runs from May 8 to 19 at the French Riviera resort.
